    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of August 22 article about Russian officials' suspicions that submarine Kursk sank after collision; Marshal Igor Sergeyev did not say that Kursk had shot buoy to surface as warning of trouble</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article yesterday about Russian officials' suspicions that the submarine Kursk sank after a collision, probably with a foreign submarine, referred incorrectly to a comment by Russia's defense minister, Marshal Igor D. Sergeyev, about a buoy observed at the site. He said Russian lookouts had seen a signal buoy of the type used by Western fleets to send emergency messages to their bases. He did not say the Kursk had shot a buoy to the surface to warn that it was in trouble.</p>
      </block>
